July 10, 2026 (continued — module standardization)

- Extended assert.util.ts with two cross-module helpers: assertBookingExists,
  assertWorkerProfileExists; eliminated 4+ duplicate private copies across services
- Extracted per-module constants: bookings.constants.ts (ROLE_REQUIREMENTS,
  CONTACT_REVEAL_STATUSES), admin.constants.ts (STRIKE_SUSPENSION_THRESHOLD),
  categories.constants.ts (CATEGORY_ORDER)
- Refactored bookings.service.ts: imports constants from bookings.constants.ts,
  uses assertBookingExists from shared util, replaced void async IIFE notify() with
  void this.resolveAndNotify().catch(() => {}), added section dividers
- Refactored admin.service.ts: imports STRIKE_SUSPENSION_THRESHOLD from
  admin.constants.ts, uses assertWorkerProfileExists for strikeWorker, added dividers
- Refactored categories.service.ts: imports CATEGORY_ORDER from categories.constants.ts
- Refactored reviews.service.ts: uses assertBookingExists and assertWorkerProfileExists
  from shared util; removed duplicate private assertion methods
- Refactored workers.service.ts: replaced Prisma.TransactionClient with TransactionClient
  from internal prismaNamespace (consistent with other services), aligned section dividers
- Documented module conventions in CLAUDE.md and .claude/commands/implement.md:
  file layout, section dividers, shared utilities, notification fire-and-forget rule
- Applied ESLint auto-format across codebase

