July 10, 2026 (continued — codebase standardization refactor)

- Standardized assertion class naming: all classes now follow [Name]Assertions pattern
  (dropped "Service" suffix from BookingsAssertionsService, UsersAssertionsService,
  CategoriesAssertionsService); renamed files to plural form (users.assertions.ts,
  categories.assertions.ts)
- Changed assertXExists methods to return the entity instead of void — eliminates
  redundant DB fetches at call sites and removes silent runtime bugs
- Fixed critical DI bug: UsersModule was exporting UsersAssertions without providing it
- Fixed admin.assertions.ts wrong import (prisma/browser → prisma/client); added
  assertWorkerProfileExists replacing standalone function in deleted assert.util.ts
- Wired UsersModule into BookingsModule and WorkersModule imports so DI resolves correctly
- Extracted ReviewsAssertions from inline validation in ReviewsService (assertBookingExistsAndCompleted, assertCustomerOwnsBooking)
- Added private readonly to all service constructor params
- Added section headers to ReviewsService; removed empty assert.util.ts
- Updated all spec files to mock new assertion class names and patterns

---

July 10, 2026 (continued — per-module assertions classes)

- Created BookingsAssertions, AdminAssertions, WorkersAssertions as @Injectable() classes
  in [name].assertions.ts; each holds all module-specific assertion methods (validate + throw)
- Updated bookings.module.ts, admin.module.ts, workers.module.ts to register assertions
  classes in providers
- Refactored bookings.service.ts, admin.service.ts, workers.service.ts: inject assertions
  class via constructor; replace this.assertX() with this.assertions.assertX(); remove
  private assertion methods and Private: assertions divider (now only two dividers per service)
- Updated all spec files to mock assertions class entirely, eliminating deep prisma mock
  chains for assertion-path tests; fixed bookings.controller.spec.ts to also provide
  BookingsAssertions mock
- Updated CLAUDE.md module conventions and .claude/commands/implement.md with assertions
  class pattern and two-divider service structure rule

